        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Take half a Pound of Pistato-Nuts, break them, and blanch the Kernels, and beat all ( except a Dozen, that you must keep to slice, to lay on the Top of the Cream ) with a little Milk; then put them into a Pint of Cream, with the Yolks of two Eggs, and sweeten it with fine Sugar : To this Quantity put a Spoonful of the Juice of Spinage, stamp ’ d and strain ’ d; set it all over the Fire, and let it just boil; and when you send it up, put the slic ’ d Kernels on the Top. If you like it thick, you may put in the White of one Egg. </p>
            </div>
